In every meeting there is a lecture where theoretical principles of organisational behaviour are introduced and seminar where practical tasks are solved.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the principles of organisational behaviour in order to support understanding, analysing and directing one's own and others' behaviour at work context.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have successfully pass this course: - Understand human behaviour in the workplace from an individual, group, and organizational perspective. - Know principles of job crafting and is able to use their principles for motivating oneself and others at work - Know the specifics of work related attitudes - Know teamwork principles and can recognize and direct different group processes - Understands the nature of organisational culture - Can analyse and direct human behaviour in context of organisational change
